<br>
The people who have problems with this usually did not put one point into each specialization.  For some reason, you can not advance any specialization past 50 unless you have at least one point in each specialization.  If you wait until 51st level or later to learn a specialization, the previously learned specializations are locked at 50 and the latest one learned is greater than 50 and becomes your &quot;Master&quot; specialization.  <br>
<br>
IE, if you haven't put at least one point into each specialization before you reach 51st level, you will have to do the specialization quest to get the specialization you want. <br>
<br>
Note of all you mages.  Put a point into each specialization at level 20 and watch them.  If the one you want to specialize in falls behind another skill, just cast a spell of that type repeatedly.  <br>
<br>
Good luck<br>
